[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Hey everyone, welcome. In this video, I\'m going to walk you through my node and show you everything it can do. If you\'re new to ComfyUI, don\'t worry. I\'ll show you how to get everything set up in just a few seconds. So, go to comfy.org, hit download local,'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'then install from GitHub, and click the direct download link. While it\'s downloading, create a folder called ComfyUI on your drive. Then just unzip the file in there, and that\'s it.'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now, you\'ll need to grab a few model files: a diffusion model, a text encoder, a VAE, and a face swap Lora. If you also want the remove background'

[00:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'feature, you\'ll need one more model for that, but that one is optional. You\'ll find all the download links on my GitHub page. One thing to keep in mind, the 9B models require you to request access on Hugging Face first. You\'ll need an'

[00:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'account for that, and once you\'re logged in, just hit the request access button. It\'s because they\'re released under a non-commercial license, so Black Forest Labs just needs you to agree to the terms. In practice, this just means the model itself isn\'t for commercial use,'

[01:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'but anything you generate with it is yours, including commercially. The only real restrictions are you can\'t use it to train a competing model, and obviously, the usual stuff: no illegal or infringing content. There\'s also a 4B'

[01:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'version of the model, smaller, faster, and a great fit if you run a weaker machine. No access requests needed there. It\'s released under Apache 2.0, so it\'s fully open for both the model'

[01:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and its outputs, including commercial use. All right, once the download is complete, move the model files into the correct ComfyUI directories. &gt;&gt; [music]'

[01:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; Now, open the ComfyUI folder, go into custom nodes, [music] and open a terminal there. Just click the address bar, type cmd, and hit enter. Then run these two commands from my GitHub page.'

[01:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The first one is to clone my node, and the second one is an additional node you\'ll need for in painting and out painting to work. Let\'s finally get generating. Launch ComfyUI, create an empty canvas, and double-click to open the node search.'

[02:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Type one node, and you\'ll see it pop up. Just select it. The first thing you\'ll want to do is head into settings and pick your downloaded models from the drop-downs. And that\'s it. Everything is ready to'

[02:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'go. One last tip. Go into ComfyUI settings and turn off nodes 2.0. Otherwise, some features might not work as expected. Now, let\'s go through everything the node can do, one mode at a time.'

[02:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'So, the first one is text to image, the classic. Type a prompt, set your image size, hit generate, and that\'s it. Your prompts can be saved and accessed later through the discover button, where'

[02:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you can basically create presets. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; You can use them instantly or turn on edit mode to update or delete them anytime.'

[02:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Next up is image to image. This one is'

[03:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'great when you have an image you mostly like but want to tweak. Maybe the composition is good, but something feels off, or you just want to explore a few variations. So, let\'s take our generated image, click use as, and select image to'

[03:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'image. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; Then describe what you want, and there\'s a strength slider that controls how much the output differs from the original. Keep it low for subtle changes, or push it higher, and the image starts shifting more dramatically.'

[03:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; Now, let\'s look at edit mode. Again, you can click use as, and this time select edit image one. This mode lets you change pretty much anything in the image. Swap the swimsuit'

[03:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'for a dress, replace the ocean with a desert, add a hat, whatever you can describe. One quick note on image sizing. By default, the output size is taken from image one. You notice the resolution label underneath it is highlighted.'

[04:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Click it to deactivate and you can either pick a preset from the drop-down or choose custom and set your own width and height. There\'s also a second image slot where you can bring another image into the mix. For example, put yourself'

[04:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'in a wedding photo with Sydney Sweeney or something. You get the idea. If you hit the discover button, you\'ll find a few presets I put together that you can play around with. You can easily change the lighting of'

[04:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the scene or switch up the style of your image. And maybe you have a Laura model with a specific style you want to use. No problem. Just click add Laura and pick'

[04:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'from the ones you have downloaded. I have an Arcane style Laura here, so let\'s use that. Okay, that\'s definitely giving Arcane vibes, but some Laura models require a'

[04:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'trigger word to actually activate the style. This note will try to load the trigger word automatically from the Laura, but that doesn\'t always work. So, it\'s always worth checking the author\'s instructions. If they list a trigger'

[05:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'word, copy it and save it in the note and from that point on it will fire automatically every time you use that Laura. &gt;&gt; [music]'

[05:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; All right, now back to the presets. Hit discover or just press D on your keyboard. One of them is enhance. This one is great for improving the quality of low quality images. I would recommend pairing it with a'

[05:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Laura and also bumping up the output resolution since that effectively gives you an upscale at the same time. Personally, I\'ve been really happy with the Adonis Laura\'s. Specifically, Adonis refine works great at a strength of 1.5,'

[05:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'but it\'s definitely worth trying different combinations and experimenting a bit to see what works for you. Another interesting preset is for'

[05:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'editing text in your image. Just describe in the prompt which text you want to replace and what it should say instead. &gt;&gt; [music]'

[06:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; There\'s also a try-on preset where you load your image and then drop in a second one with the outfit you want to'

[06:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'put on. It works best when the clothing is on its own or at least without another person\'s face in the shot. &gt;&gt; [music]'

[06:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; And if the result isn\'t quite what you expected, adding a description of the'

[07:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'clothing in the prompt can help a lot. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; And the last preset I\'ll mention is texture transfer. It does exactly what'

[07:19] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'the name suggests. Pretty fun to play with. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; Now, let\'s get to my favorite mode,'

[07:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'paint. On top of inpainting and outpainting, which I\'ll get to in a moment, you can also just sketch something out and turn it into a realistic scene or whatever style you\'re going for. I love this one because you have real control over the composition'

[07:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and you don\'t need to be an artist. A rough sketch is more than enough. So, sketch it out, describe your scene, and hit generate. &gt;&gt; [music]'

[08:07] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; You can also add real images to the'

[08:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'canvas and build a scene from actual photos. Earlier, I mentioned the background removal model. If you downloaded it, this is what it comes in. Click the plus button in the layers panel and you\'ll see two options, blank layer or image layer. Pick image layer'

[08:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and choose the photo you want to bring in. You\'ll then see a remove background button. Click it and the model takes care of the rest. Arrange your composition however you like and hit save. Then open discover and you\'ll find a preset I made called'

[08:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'collage to scene. Select it, describe your scene in the prompt, and you can create something like a Vogue magazine cover just like that. Okay, now let\'s look at in-painting and out-painting. I haven\'t mentioned it'

[09:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'yet, but you\'ve probably noticed the gallery. That\'s where all your generated images live. You get a grid view and when you open a specific image, you can see all the details. With one click, you can load all the settings back into the'

[09:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'main UI or drop the image straight into whichever mode you want to use it in. You can also save images to favorites or delete the ones you don\'t like directly'

[09:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'from there. But, let\'s try in-paint. I\'ll grab an image from the gallery and use it as the input for the paint slot. In in paint mode, you just paint over the area you want to change, save the'

[09:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'mask, describe what you want in the prompt, and that\'s [music] it. &gt;&gt; [music]'

[09:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; Now, let me grab a different image from the gallery and show you how out painting works. I\'ll zoom out a bit and you can see that on all four edges of the image you can drag to expand the canvas, basically'

[10:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'extending the scene beyond its original borders. Set how much you want to expand and one small [music] tip, I\'d recommend doing one direction at a time. The lime colored text shows you what the final'

[10:20] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'image size will be after the expansion. If that\'s too large for your machine to handle, there\'s an option to scale down the output resolution. Confirm your changes and let\'s look at the prompt. I\'d recommend describing what you want'

[10:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to appear in the expanded area. For example, if I write that the woman should be wearing a one-piece swimsuit, it looks like this. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; And if I switch it to a two-piece, you get something like this.'

[10:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'And the last mode, face swap. Make sure you have the right Laura selected in settings and you\'re good to go. It\'s straightforward. Upload the image with the face you want to replace into target and the new face into source. Simple as'

[10:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that. &gt;&gt; [music] &gt;&gt; Now, let\'s go over the keyboard'

[11:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'shortcuts real quick. You can see them in the bottom left corner and I think once you get used to them, they\'ll speed up your whole workflow. One thing to watch out for, the shortcuts only work when your mouse is actually inside the'

[11:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'node. D, which I already mentioned, opens Discover for browsing and selecting presets. F gives you a full-screen preview of the last generated image. G opens the gallery. Press the same key again and you\'re back'

[11:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to the main interface. After typing your prompt, hit escape to exit the text area and then space to start generating right away. Almost forgot, settings has a toggle to unlock advanced controls like seed or sampler for anyone who wants'

[11:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'more control. I personally never touched it. The defaults work great. But hey, it\'s your node now, so go wild. Stable Diffusion XL is a genuinely impressive model and there\'s a lot more you can do with it than what I showed here, but I'

[12:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'hope this gave you at least some inspiration. If you found this useful, any support means a lot to me. And if you\'re curious what else I\'m cooking up, I\'m already working on something similar for LTX 2.3, so don\'t go too far. Thank you and I\'ll see you in the next one.'

[12:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '&gt;&gt; I\'m scared of you. &gt;&gt; DON\'T BE AFRAID. I JUST WANT TO BE YOUR FRIEND. &gt;&gt; [laughter]'
